    "-> TruthLink: The Data Truth Audit\n",
    "The Problem:\n",
    "Most business decisions are made using Raw Data that hasn't been cleaned. Small system glitches like a button being clicked twice or a form being left blank can trick a manager into making a million dollar mistake.\n",
    "\n",
    "My Objective\n",
    "I built this audit to find the Lies in the Data. By comparing a messy dataset to the actual truth, I calculated exactly how much these little glitches distort our most important business numbers.\n",
    "\n",
    "-> The Distortion Findings and Their Impact\n",
    "Revenue Overestimation (+20.7%)\n",
    "What happened: System errors recorded some sales twice.\n",
    "The Risk: The company thinks it has more money than it actually does. This leads to overspending and hiring people the company cannot afford.\n",
    "\n",
    "The Return Rate False Alarm (+44.7%)\n",
    "What happened: The system forgot to mark some successful orders, making them look like failures.\n",
    "The Risk: Management might panic and think 1 in 3 customers is unhappy when in reality the product is doing great.\n",
    "\n",
    "Average Sale Inflation (+11.7%)\n",
    "What happened: A few glitchy high prices pulled the average up.\n",
    "The Risk: Marketing might try to target luxury shoppers who do not actually exist in this dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
